refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
stringfalseiconv_substr stringstr intoffset intlengthiconv_strlen($str, $charset) stringcharsetini_get("iconv.internal_encoding")
Cuts a portion of str specified by the offset and length parameters.

&reftitle.returnvalues;
Returns the portion of str specified by the offset and length parameters.
If str is shorter than offset characters long, &false; will be returned. If str is exactly offset characters long, an empty string will be returned.

&reftitle.changelog;







     &Version;
     &Description;





     7.0.11

      If str is equal to
      offset characters long, an empty string will be
      returned. Prior to this version, &false; was returned in this case.
